Master

   Master's programmes at the Faculty of Humanities cover disciplines within language and literature, history and philosophy, and aesthetical and practical-aesthetical disciplines.

   We also offer international master's programmes in English Language and Linguistics, Linguistics, Globalization and Applied Ethics.

The Faculty of Humanities offers the following two-year international master's programmes:

     * Master of Philosophy (M. Phil.) in Linguistics
     * M. Phil. in English Linguistics and Language Acquisition
     * Erasmus Mundus Master in Dance Knowledge Practice and Heritage: Choreomundus

   Students attending international master's programmes are exempted from Norwegian language requirements.

Other master's programmes:

   Candidates who wish to attend our master's programmes listed below are not exempted from Norwegian language requirements. Detailed programme descriptions of the master's programmes listed below
   are available here in alphabetical order.

Disciplines within language and literature:

     * English (all courses are taught in English)
     * French (all courses are taught in French)
     * German (all courses are taught in German)
     * Scandinavian Language and Literature
     * Linguistics (all courses at intermediate and master's level are taught in English)
     * Phonetics
     * Language and Communication Studies (aka. 'Applied Linguistics')

Disciplines within history, culture and ideas:

     * Archaeology
     * Philosophy
          + Philosophy
          + Philosophy with specialization in Applied Ethics
     * History
          + History
          + Classical Studies
     * Religious Studies

Aesthetical and practical-aesthetical disciplines:

     * Art History
     * Dance Studies
     * Drama and Theatre
     * Film Studies
     * Media Production
     * Media Studies: Visual Culture
     * Music Performance
     * Musicology

Interdisciplinary two-year master's programmes:

     * Art Criticism and Cultural Dissemination
     * Cultural Heritage
     * European Studies
     * Interdisciplinary Studies of Culture
     * Music Technology

